 interface ArrayTypeDeclarator
          This PrimaryExpression type represents an array type declarator.
 interface BinaryOperatorExpression
          This Expression type represents all kinds of binary operator expressions.
 interface ClassConstructorCall

 interface ConditionalExpression
          This Expression type represents a conditional expression, i.e.
 interface DotExpression
          This PrimaryExpression type represents a chain of primary expressions separated by dots.
 interface ExplicitConstructorCall
          This PrimaryExpression type represents an explicit this or super constructor call.
 interface Identifier
          This PrimaryExpression type represents a simple identifier expression, i.e. such an expression is nothing else than a not qualified identifier.
 interface InstanceofExpression
          This Expression type represents an instanceof expression
 interface Literal
          This PrimaryExpression represents a literal.
 interface MethodCall
          This PrimaryExpression type represents a method invocation.
 interface ParenthesizedExpression
          This Expression type represents a parenthesized expression, i.e.
 interface PrimaryExpression
          This JSOM type is the base type for all kinds of expressions that are not of arithmetic or logical nature; i.e. a primary expression represents things like literals, method calls, new expressions, and so on.
 interface PrimaryExpressionKeyword
          This PrimaryExpression type represents the most trivial kinds of primary expressions which are the keywords class, this , super or void.
 interface StaticArrayCreator
          This PrimaryExpression type represents a new expression for creating static arrays.
 interface TypeCast
          This Expression type represents a type cast.
 interface UnaryOperatorExpression
          This Expression type represents all kinds of unary operator expressions.
